     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>Ad Lectorem.</head>
   <l>GO princely writ apparelled in loue,</l>
   <l>The poyson of all sorrowes to remooue:</l>
   <l>Inrich thy selfe and me by thy selfe riches,</l>
   <l>And striue to mount beyond our Poets pitches.</l>
   <l>And thou kind <hi>Reader,</hi> reading this my writ,</l>
   <l>Applaud the inuention of an infant wit.</l>
   <l>Though yoong it be, it hath as good a hart,</l>
   <l>To merite well, as those of high desart.</l>
   <l>Then blame it not although for Fame it striue,</l>
   <l>For after death Fame still remaines aliue.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Thine in all loue, <hi>H. P.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
</div>
